I have used Maps since 2013 when I got my first Galaxy phone.  It was and still is an excellent gps navigation software.  The only reason I give it a 4 star is that over time, there appears to be some fraying at the seams.  1.  First, starting approximately around the time of the Oreo release, the app has bloated to the point that it now takes exceptionally long to load and it has become generally very sluggish.  It still works great once it starts.  2. Second, voice navigation over bluetooth is now partly broken (though this may be because of Oreo's issues with the older BT standards rather than the app itself).  Specifically, the voice instructions truncate over BT unless there is another app that keeps BT active (e.g. playing music via an app or running some of the apps designed to work around this problem).
